{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"My name is Arvind Gupta, and I'm a toymaker."},{"time":3000,"text":"I've been making toys for the last 30 years."},{"time":6000,"text":"The early '70s, I was in college."},{"time":8000,"text":"It was a very revolutionary time."},{"time":10000,"text":"It was a political ferment, so to say --"},{"time":13000,"text":"students out in the streets of Paris,"},{"time":15000,"text":"revolting against authority."},{"time":17000,"text":"America was jolted"},{"time":19000,"text":"by the anti-Vietnam movement, the Civil Rights movement."},{"time":22000,"text":"In India, we had the Naxalite movement,"},{"time":25000,"text":"the [unclear] movement."},{"time":27000,"text":"But you know, when there is a political churning of society,"},{"time":29000,"text":"it unleashes a lot of energy."},{"time":32000,"text":"The National Movement of India"},{"time":34000,"text":"was testimony to that."},{"time":36000,"text":"Lots of people resigned from well-paid jobs"},{"time":40000,"text":"and jumped into the National Movement."},{"time":42000,"text":"Now in the early '70s,"},{"time":44000,"text":"one of the great programs in India"},{"time":46000,"text":"was to revitalize"},{"time":48000,"text":"primary science in village schools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50000,"text":"There was a person, Anil Sadgopal, did a Ph.D. from Caltech"},{"time":53000,"text":"and returned back as a molecular biologist"},{"time":55000,"text":"in India's cutting-edge research institute, the TIFR."},{"time":58000,"text":"At 31, he was not able"},{"time":60000,"text":"to relate the kind of [unclear] research,"},{"time":62000,"text":"which he was doing with the lives of the ordinary people."},{"time":65000,"text":"So he designed and went and started a village science program."},{"time":68000,"text":"Many people were inspired by this."},{"time":70000,"text":"The slogan of the early '70s"},{"time":72000,"text":"was \"Go to the people."},{"time":74000,"text":"Live with them; love them."},{"time":76000,"text":"Start from what they know. Build on what they have.\""},{"time":79000,"text":"This was kind of the defining slogan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81000,"text":"Well I took one year."},{"time":83000,"text":"I joined Telco, made TATA trucks, pretty close to Pune."},{"time":86000,"text":"I worked there for two years,"},{"time":88000,"text":"and I realized that I was not born to make trucks."},{"time":91000,"text":"Often one doesn't know what one wants to do,"},{"time":93000,"text":"but it's good enough to know what you don't want to do."},{"time":95000,"text":"So I took one year off, and I went to this village science program."},{"time":98000,"text":"And it was a turning point."},{"time":100000,"text":"It was a very small village --"},{"time":102000,"text":"a weekly bazaar"},{"time":104000,"text":"where people, just once in a week, they put in all the vats."},{"time":107000,"text":"So I said, \"I'm going to spend a year over here.\""},{"time":109000,"text":"So I just bought one specimen"},{"time":111000,"text":"of everything which was sold on the roadside."},{"time":113000,"text":"And one thing which I found"},{"time":115000,"text":"was this black rubber."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117000,"text":"This is called a cycle valve tube."},{"time":119000,"text":"When you pump in air in a bicycle, you use a bit of this."},{"time":122000,"text":"And some of these models --"},{"time":124000,"text":"so you take a bit of this cycle valve tube,"},{"time":126000,"text":"you can put two matchsticks inside this, and you make a flexible joint."},{"time":129000,"text":"It's a joint of tubes. You start by teaching angles --"},{"time":132000,"text":"an acute angle, a right angle, an obtuse angle, a straight angle."},{"time":134000,"text":"It's like its own little coupling."},{"time":136000,"text":"If you have three of them, and you loop them together,"},{"time":138000,"text":"well you make a triangle."},{"time":140000,"text":"With four, you make a square,"},{"time":142000,"text":"you make a pentagon, you make a hexagon,"},{"time":144000,"text":"you make all these kind of polygons."},{"time":146000,"text":"And they have some wonderful properties."},{"time":148000,"text":"If you look at the hexagon, for instance,"},{"time":150000,"text":"it's like an amoeba, which is constantly changing its own profile."},{"time":153000,"text":"You can just pull this out, this becomes a rectangle."},{"time":155000,"text":"You give it a push, this becomes a parallelogram."},{"time":157000,"text":"But this is very shaky."},{"time":159000,"text":"Look at the pentagon, for instance,"},{"time":161000,"text":"pull this out -- it becomes a boat shape trapezium."},{"time":163000,"text":"Push it and it becomes house shaped."},{"time":165000,"text":"This becomes an isosceles triangle --"},{"time":167000,"text":"again, very shaky."},{"time":169000,"text":"This square might look very square and prim."},{"time":171000,"text":"Give it a little push -- this becomes a rhombus."},{"time":173000,"text":"It becomes kite-shaped."},{"time":175000,"text":"But give a child a triangle,"},{"time":177000,"text":"he can't do a thing to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179000,"text":"Why use triangles?"},{"time":181000,"text":"Because triangles are the only rigid structures."},{"time":183000,"text":"We can't make a bridge with squares"},{"time":185000,"text":"because the train would come, it would start doing a jig."},{"time":188000,"text":"Ordinary people know about this"},{"time":190000,"text":"because if you go to a village in India,"},{"time":192000,"text":"they might not have gone to engineering college,"},{"time":194000,"text":"but no one makes a roof placed like this."},{"time":196000,"text":"Because if they put tiles on top, it's just going to crash."},{"time":199000,"text":"They always make a triangular roof."},{"time":201000,"text":"Now this is people science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203000,"text":"And if you were to just poke a hole over here"},{"time":205000,"text":"and put a third matchstick,"},{"time":207000,"text":"you'll get a T joint."},{"time":209000,"text":"And if I were to poke all the three legs of this"},{"time":211000,"text":"in the three vertices of this triangle,"},{"time":213000,"text":"I would make a tetrahedron."},{"time":215000,"text":"So you make all these 3D shapes."},{"time":217000,"text":"You make a tetrahedron like this."},{"time":220000,"text":"And once you make these,"},{"time":224000,"text":"you make a little house."},{"time":228000,"text":"Put this on top."},{"time":230000,"text":"You can make a joint of four. You can make a joint of six."},{"time":232000,"text":"You just need a ton."},{"time":235000,"text":"Now this was -- you make a joint of six,"},{"time":237000,"text":"you make an icosahedron."},{"time":239000,"text":"You can play around with it."},{"time":241000,"text":"This makes an igloo."},{"time":243000,"text":"Now this is in 1978."},{"time":245000,"text":"I was a 24-year-old young engineer."},{"time":248000,"text":"And I thought this was so much better than making trucks."},{"time":252000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":257000,"text":"If you, as a matter of fact, put four marbles inside,"},{"time":260000,"text":"you simulate the molecular structure of methane, CH4."},{"time":263000,"text":"Four atoms of hydrogen, the four points of the tetrahedron,"},{"time":265000,"text":"which means the little carbon atom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267000,"text":"Well since then,"},{"time":269000,"text":"I just thought that I've been really privileged"},{"time":272000,"text":"to go to over 2,000 schools in my country --"},{"time":276000,"text":"village schools, government schools,"},{"time":278000,"text":"municipal schools, Ivy League schools --"},{"time":280000,"text":"I've been invited by most of them."},{"time":282000,"text":"And every time I go to a school,"},{"time":284000,"text":"I see a gleam in the eyes of the children."},{"time":286000,"text":"I see hope. I see happiness in their faces."},{"time":289000,"text":"Children want to make things. Children want to do things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292000,"text":"Now this, we make lots and lots of pumps."},{"time":295000,"text":"Now this is a little pump"},{"time":297000,"text":"with which you could inflate a balloon."},{"time":299000,"text":"It's a real pump. You could actually pop the balloon."},{"time":302000,"text":"And we have a slogan"},{"time":304000,"text":"that the best thing a child can do with a toy is to break it."},{"time":307000,"text":"So all you do is --"},{"time":309000,"text":"it's a very kind of provocative statement --"},{"time":311000,"text":"this old bicycle tube and this old plastic [unclear]"},{"time":313000,"text":"This filling cap will go very snugly into an old bicycle tube."},{"time":316000,"text":"And this is how you make a valve."},{"time":318000,"text":"You put a little sticky tape."},{"time":322000,"text":"This is one-way traffic."},{"time":326000,"text":"Well we make lots and lots of pumps."},{"time":328000,"text":"And this is the other one --"},{"time":330000,"text":"that you just take a straw, and you just put a stick inside"},{"time":332000,"text":"and you make two half-cuts."},{"time":334000,"text":"Now this is what you do,"},{"time":336000,"text":"is you bend both these legs into a triangle,"},{"time":338000,"text":"and you just wrap some tape around."},{"time":340000,"text":"And this is the pump."},{"time":342000,"text":"And now, if you have this pump,"},{"time":345000,"text":"it's like a great, great sprinkler."},{"time":348000,"text":"It's like a centrifuge."},{"time":350000,"text":"If you spin something, it tends to fly out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":355000,"text":"Well in terms of -- if you were in Andhra Pradesh,"},{"time":357000,"text":"you would make this with the palmyra leaf."},{"time":359000,"text":"Many of our folk toys"},{"time":361000,"text":"have great science principles."},{"time":363000,"text":"If you spin-top something, it tends to fly out."},{"time":365000,"text":"If I do it with both hands, you can see this fun Mr. Flying Man."},{"time":370000,"text":"Right."},{"time":374000,"text":"This is a toy which is made from paper. It's amazing."},{"time":377000,"text":"There are four pictures."},{"time":379000,"text":"You see insects,"},{"time":381000,"text":"you see frogs, snakes, eagles, butterflies,"},{"time":383000,"text":"frogs, snakes, eagles."},{"time":385000,"text":"Here's a paper which you could [unclear] --"},{"time":387000,"text":"designed by a mathematician at Harvard in 1928,"},{"time":389000,"text":"Arthur Stone,"},{"time":391000,"text":"documented by Martin Gardner in many of his many books."},{"time":394000,"text":"But this is great fun for children."},{"time":396000,"text":"They all study about the food chain."},{"time":398000,"text":"The insects are eaten by the frogs; the frogs are eaten by the snakes;"},{"time":400000,"text":"the snakes are eaten by the eagles."},{"time":402000,"text":"And this can be, if you had a whole photocopy paper --"},{"time":404000,"text":"A4 size paper --"},{"time":406000,"text":"you could be in a municipal school, you could be in a government school --"},{"time":409000,"text":"a paper, a scale and a pencil -- no glue, no scissors."},{"time":412000,"text":"In three minutes, you just fold this up."},{"time":415000,"text":"And what you could use it for is just limited by your imagination."},{"time":418000,"text":"If you take a smaller paper, you make a smaller flexagon."},{"time":421000,"text":"With a bigger one, you make a bigger one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426000,"text":"Now this is a pencil with a few slots over here."},{"time":428000,"text":"And you put a little fan here."},{"time":430000,"text":"And this is a hundred-year-old toy."},{"time":432000,"text":"There have been six major research papers on this."},{"time":435000,"text":"There's some grooves over here, you can see."},{"time":437000,"text":"And if I take a reed -- if I rub this,"},{"time":439000,"text":"something very amazing happens."},{"time":441000,"text":"Six major research papers on this."},{"time":443000,"text":"As a matter of fact, Feynman, as a child, was very fascinated by this."},{"time":445000,"text":"He wrote a paper on this."},{"time":447000,"text":"And you don't need the three billion-dollar Hadron Collider"},{"time":449000,"text":"for doing this. (Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":451000,"text":"This is there for every child,"},{"time":453000,"text":"and every child can enjoy this."},{"time":455000,"text":"If you want to put a colored disk,"},{"time":458000,"text":"well all these seven colors coalesce."},{"time":460000,"text":"And this is what Newton talked about 400 years back,"},{"time":463000,"text":"that white light's made of seven colors,"},{"time":465000,"text":"just by spinning this around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467000,"text":"This is a straw."},{"time":470000,"text":"What we've done, we've just sealed both the ends with tape,"},{"time":473000,"text":"nipped the right corner and the bottom left corner,"},{"time":475000,"text":"so there's holes in the opposite corners, there's a little hole over here."},{"time":478000,"text":"This is a kind of a blowing straw."},{"time":480000,"text":"I just put this inside this."},{"time":482000,"text":"There's a hole here, and I shut this."},{"time":490000,"text":"And this costs very little money to make --"},{"time":492000,"text":"great fun for children to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494000,"text":"What we do"},{"time":496000,"text":"is make a very simple electric motor."},{"time":498000,"text":"Now this is the simplest motor on Earth."},{"time":502000,"text":"The most expensive thing is the battery inside this."},{"time":505000,"text":"If you have a battery, it costs five cents to make it."},{"time":508000,"text":"This is an old bicycle tube,"},{"time":510000,"text":"which gives you a broad rubber band, two safety pins."},{"time":512000,"text":"This is a permanent magnet."},{"time":514000,"text":"Whenever current flows through the coil, this becomes an electromagnet."},{"time":517000,"text":"It's the interaction of both these magnets"},{"time":519000,"text":"which makes this motor spin."},{"time":521000,"text":"We made 30,000."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523000,"text":"Teachers who have been teaching science for donkey years,"},{"time":526000,"text":"they just muck up the definition and they spit it out."},{"time":529000,"text":"When teachers make it, children make it."},{"time":531000,"text":"You can see a gleam in their eye."},{"time":533000,"text":"They get a thrill"},{"time":536000,"text":"of what science is all about."},{"time":538000,"text":"And this science is not a rich man's game."},{"time":540000,"text":"In a democratic country,"},{"time":542000,"text":"science must reach to our most oppressed,"},{"time":545000,"text":"to the most marginalized children."},{"time":547000,"text":"This program started with 16 schools"},{"time":550000,"text":"and spread to 1,500 government schools."},{"time":553000,"text":"Over 100,000 children learn science this way."},{"time":557000,"text":"And we're just trying to see possibilities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":559000,"text":"Look, this is the tetrapak --"},{"time":561000,"text":"awful materials from the point of view of the environment."},{"time":564000,"text":"There are six layers -- three layers of plastic, aluminum --"},{"time":567000,"text":"which are are sealed together."},{"time":569000,"text":"They are fused together, so you can't separate them."},{"time":571000,"text":"Now you can just make a little network like this"},{"time":573000,"text":"and fold them and stick them together"},{"time":575000,"text":"and make an icosahedron."},{"time":577000,"text":"So something which is trash,"},{"time":579000,"text":"which is choking all the seabirds,"},{"time":582000,"text":"you could just recycle this into a very, very joyous --"},{"time":585000,"text":"all the platonic solids can be made with things like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588000,"text":"This is a little straw,"},{"time":591000,"text":"and what you do is you just nip two corners here,"},{"time":595000,"text":"and this becomes like a baby crocodile's mouth."},{"time":599000,"text":"You put this in your mouth, and you blow."},{"time":601000,"text":"(Honk)"},{"time":603000,"text":"It's children's delight, a teacher's envy, as they say."},{"time":607000,"text":"You're not able to see how the sound is produced,"},{"time":609000,"text":"because the thing which is vibrating goes inside my mouth."},{"time":612000,"text":"I'm going to keep this outside, to blow out. I'm going to suck in air."},{"time":615000,"text":"(Honk)"},{"time":617000,"text":"So no one actually needs to muck up the production of sound"},{"time":620000,"text":"with wire vibrations."},{"time":622000,"text":"The other is that you keep blowing at it,"},{"time":624000,"text":"keep making the sound,"},{"time":626000,"text":"and you keep cutting it."},{"time":628000,"text":"And something very, very nice happens."},{"time":630000,"text":"(Honk)"},{"time":642000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":645000,"text":"And when you get a very small one --"},{"time":647000,"text":"(Honk)"},{"time":650000,"text":"This is what the kids teach you. You can also do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653000,"text":"Well before I go any further,"},{"time":655000,"text":"this is something worth sharing."},{"time":657000,"text":"This is a touching slate meant for blind children."},{"time":659000,"text":"This is strips of Velcro, this is my drawing slate,"},{"time":662000,"text":"and this is my drawing pen,"},{"time":664000,"text":"which is basically a film box."},{"time":666000,"text":"It's basically like a fisherman's line,"},{"time":670000,"text":"a fishing line."},{"time":672000,"text":"And this is wool over here."},{"time":674000,"text":"If I crank the handle, all the wool goes inside."},{"time":677000,"text":"And what a blind child can do is to just draw this."},{"time":681000,"text":"Wool sticks on Velcro."},{"time":685000,"text":"There are 12 million blind children in our country --"},{"time":688000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":690000,"text":"who live in a world of darkness."},{"time":692000,"text":"And this has come as a great boon to them."},{"time":695000,"text":"There's a factory out there making our children blind,"},{"time":698000,"text":"not able to provide them with food,"},{"time":700000,"text":"not able to provide them with vitamin A."},{"time":702000,"text":"But this has come as a great boon for them."},{"time":704000,"text":"There are no patents. Anyone can make it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":708000,"text":"This is very, very simple."},{"time":710000,"text":"You can see, this is the generator. It's a crank generator."},{"time":713000,"text":"These are two magnets."},{"time":715000,"text":"This is a large pulley made by sandwiching rubber between two old CDs."},{"time":718000,"text":"Small pulley and two strong magnets."},{"time":720000,"text":"And this fiber turns a wire attached to an LED."},{"time":723000,"text":"If I spin this pulley, the small one's going to spin much faster."},{"time":725000,"text":"There will be a spinning magnetic field."},{"time":727000,"text":"Lines, of course, would be cut, the force will be generated."},{"time":730000,"text":"And you can see, this LED is going to glow."},{"time":732000,"text":"So this is a small crank generator."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736000,"text":"Well, this is, again,"},{"time":739000,"text":"it's just a ring, a steel ring with steel nuts."},{"time":742000,"text":"And what you can do"},{"time":744000,"text":"is just, if you give it a twirl,"},{"time":747000,"text":"well they just keep going on."},{"time":753000,"text":"And imagine a bunch of kids"},{"time":755000,"text":"standing in a circle"},{"time":757000,"text":"and just waiting for the steel ring to be passed on."},{"time":759000,"text":"And they'd be absolutely joyous playing with this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764000,"text":"Well in the end, what we can also do:"},{"time":766000,"text":"we use a lot of old newspapers"},{"time":769000,"text":"to make caps."},{"time":771000,"text":"This is worthy of Sachin Tendulkar."},{"time":773000,"text":"It's a great cricket cap. (Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":776000,"text":"When first you see Nehru and Gandhi,"},{"time":778000,"text":"this is the Nehru cap -- just half a newspaper."},{"time":781000,"text":"We make lots of toys with newspapers,"},{"time":783000,"text":"and this is one of them."},{"time":785000,"text":"And this is -- you can see --"},{"time":787000,"text":"this is a flapping bird."},{"time":790000,"text":"All of our old newspapers, we cut them into little squares."},{"time":793000,"text":"And if you have one of these birds --"},{"time":795000,"text":"children in Japan have been making this bird for many, many years."},{"time":800000,"text":"And you can see,"},{"time":802000,"text":"this is a little fantail bird."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806000,"text":"Well in the end, I'll just end with a story."},{"time":809000,"text":"This is called \"The Captain's Hat Story.\""},{"time":811000,"text":"The captain was a captain of a sea-going ship."},{"time":813000,"text":"It goes very slowly."},{"time":815000,"text":"And there were lots of passengers on the ship,"},{"time":817000,"text":"and they were getting bored, so the captain invited them on the deck."},{"time":819000,"text":"\"Wear all your colorful clothes and sing and dance,"},{"time":821000,"text":"and I'll provide you with good food and drinks.\""},{"time":823000,"text":"And the captain would wear a cap everyday"},{"time":825000,"text":"and join in the regalia."},{"time":827000,"text":"The first day, it was a huge umbrella cap,"},{"time":829000,"text":"like a captain's cap."},{"time":831000,"text":"That night, when the passengers would be sleeping,"},{"time":834000,"text":"he would give it one more fold,"},{"time":836000,"text":"and the second day, he would be wearing a fireman's cap --"},{"time":838000,"text":"with a little shoot just like a designer cap,"},{"time":840000,"text":"because it protects the spinal cord."},{"time":843000,"text":"And the second night, he would take the same cap"},{"time":845000,"text":"and give it another fold."},{"time":847000,"text":"And the third day, it would be a Shikari cap --"},{"time":849000,"text":"just like an adventurer's cap."},{"time":852000,"text":"And the third night, he would give it two more folds --"},{"time":855000,"text":"and this is a very, very famous cap."},{"time":857000,"text":"If you've seen any of our Bollywood films,"},{"time":859000,"text":"this is what the policeman wears,"},{"time":861000,"text":"it's called a zapalu cap."},{"time":863000,"text":"It's been catapulted to international glory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":866000,"text":"And we must not forget that he was the captain of the ship."},{"time":869000,"text":"So that's a ship."},{"time":871000,"text":"And now the end:"},{"time":873000,"text":"everyone was enjoying the journey very much."},{"time":875000,"text":"They were singing and dancing."},{"time":877000,"text":"Suddenly there was a storm and huge waves."},{"time":880000,"text":"And all the ship can do is to dance and pitch along with the waves."},{"time":883000,"text":"A huge wave comes and slaps the front"},{"time":885000,"text":"and knocks it down."},{"time":887000,"text":"And another one comes and slaps the aft and knocks it down."},{"time":890000,"text":"And there's a third one over here."},{"time":892000,"text":"This swallows the bridge and knocks it down."},{"time":894000,"text":"And the ship sinks,"},{"time":896000,"text":"and the captain has lost everything,"},{"time":898000,"text":"but for a life jacket."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901000,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":903000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}